---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy | CryptoBonusList" description="How CryptoBonusList handles your data. Plain language, no legal filler.">
  <section class="px-6 py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-4">
        PRIVACY <span class="text-[#39FF14]">POLICY</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] text-sm mb-10">
        Last updated: March 1, 2026
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10">
        <!-- Section 1 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            1. WHAT WE COLLECT
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We collect minimal data. Here is what we gather and why:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Analytics data:</strong> Page views, referral sources, device type, browser type, screen resolution, and approximate geographic region (country level). We use this to understand which content is useful and where our readers are located. No personal identification is attached to analytics data.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Contact form submissions:</strong> If you send us a message through the contact page, we store your email address, subject line, and message content. This data is stored for the purpose of responding to your inquiry.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Cookies:</strong> We use essential cookies for site functionality and analytics cookies to track anonymous usage patterns. See Section 4 for a full breakdown.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Server logs:</strong> Our hosting provider automatically collects IP addresses, request timestamps, and page URLs in server access logs. These logs are retained for security and diagnostics. They are purged within 30 days.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Click events:</strong> When you click an affiliate link, we record which link was clicked and the page you clicked it from. This is used to measure the performance of our content. The click data does not include personally identifiable information.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We do not collect names, physical addresses, phone numbers, payment information, wallet addresses, or government IDs. We do not require account registration. There is no login system on this site.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 2 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            2. HOW WE USE YOUR DATA
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Analytics data helps us see which pages get traffic and which content people find useful. We use this to decide what to write about and what to improve. For example, if a bonus review gets high traffic, we prioritize keeping that page updated.
            </p>
            <p>
              Contact form data is used strictly to reply to your message. We do not add your email to any mailing list. We do not send promotional emails. We do not share your email with casinos. One reply, done.
            </p>
            <p>
              Server log data is used for security monitoring. If we detect unusual traffic patterns that suggest an attack or scraping attempt, we use log data to identify and block the source.
            </p>
            <p>
              Affiliate click data is aggregated and anonymized. We use it to understand which bonuses our readers are interested in. No individual user profile is built from click data.
            </p>
            <p>
              We do not use your data for automated decision-making or profiling. We do not run any algorithm that targets ads to you based on your behavior on this site. We do not display ads.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 3 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            3. AFFILIATE LINKS AND THIRD PARTIES
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              This site contains affiliate links to crypto casinos and gambling platforms. When you click these links, you leave our site and enter a third-party platform.
            </p>
            <p>
              We have no control over how those platforms handle your data. Each casino has its own privacy policy, data retention practices, and KYC requirements. Read theirs before signing up. This is especially relevant for crypto casinos that require identity verification.
            </p>
            <p>
              Affiliate link clicks are tracked to attribute referrals. This tracking uses cookies set by the casino's affiliate program, not by us. These third-party cookies are placed on your device when you click an outbound link. We do not control their duration or what data they collect.
            </p>
            <p>
              The third-party services that interact with this site include:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Analytics provider:</strong> Processes anonymized usage statistics. Does not receive personal data.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Hosting provider:</strong> Serves the website files and collects standard server logs.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Casino affiliate programs:</strong> Track referrals through their own cookies when you click outbound links.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Google Fonts:</strong> Fonts are loaded from Google servers. Google receives your IP address as part of serving the font files.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We do not embed social media widgets, share buttons, or tracking pixels from social networks.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 4 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            4. COOKIES
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Cookies are small text files stored on your device by your browser. We use them for limited purposes. Here is the full breakdown:
            </p>
            <div class="border-[3px] border-white bg-black p-4 mt-2">
              <table class="w-full text-sm">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="border-b-2 border-white">
                    <th class="text-left text-white font-[Space_Grotesk] py-2 pr-4">Type</th>
                    <th class="text-left text-white font-[Space_Grotesk] py-2 pr-4">Purpose</th>
                    <th class="text-left text-white font-[Space_Grotesk] py-2 pr-4">Duration</th>
                    <th class="text-left text-white font-[Space_Grotesk] py-2">Set By</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="text-[#D4D4D4]">
                  <tr class="border-b border-gray-700">
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Essential</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Site functionality, preferences</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Session</td>
                    <td class="py-2">Us</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-gray-700">
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Analytics</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Anonymous page view tracking</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 year</td>
                    <td class="py-2">Us</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-gray-700">
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Affiliate</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Referral attribution for casinos</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">30-90 days</td>
                    <td class="py-2">Third party</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Font loading</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">Cache font assets locally</td>
                    <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 year</td>
                    <td class="py-2">Google</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <p>
              You control cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers let you block all cookies, block third-party cookies only, or clear cookies on exit. Blocking analytics cookies does not affect site functionality.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you block all cookies, the site will still work. It is a static site. No login, no preferences to save, no shopping cart.
            </p>
            <p>
              For instructions on managing cookies in your browser:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Chrome:</strong> Settings &gt; Privacy and Security &gt; Cookies</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Firefox:</strong> Settings &gt; Privacy &amp; Security &gt; Cookies and Site Data</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Safari:</strong> Preferences &gt; Privacy &gt; Manage Website Data</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Edge:</strong> Settings &gt; Cookies and Site Permissions</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 5 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            5. DATA STORAGE AND SECURITY
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              This is a static website. We do not run a database that stores user accounts, passwords, or personal profiles. There is no backend application processing user data in real time.
            </p>
            <p>
              Contact form submissions are stored in a secure email system with encrypted access. Analytics data is processed by our analytics provider on their infrastructure. We do not sell, trade, rent, or transfer your data to anyone for marketing purposes.
            </p>
            <p>
              The site is served over HTTPS. All data transmitted between your browser and our servers is encrypted in transit using TLS.
            </p>
            <p>
              We retain contact form data for up to 12 months after the last correspondence, then delete it. Analytics data is retained in aggregated form indefinitely. Server logs are purged within 30 days.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 6 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            6. DATA SHARING
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We do not sell your data. We do not share it with advertisers. We do not share it with casinos.
            </p>
            <p>
              The only circumstances where we would share data:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Legal obligation:</strong> If required by law, court order, or regulatory authority, we would comply with requests for data. We would limit disclosure to what is legally required.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Service providers:</strong> Our hosting and analytics providers process data on our behalf under their own privacy policies. They do not have independent rights to use or sell the data.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Business transfer:</strong> If CryptoBonusList is acquired or merged, data would transfer to the new owner under the same privacy obligations described here.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 7 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            7. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Our servers and service providers operate in various countries. If you access this site from the European Economic Area (EEA), UK, or other jurisdictions with data transfer restrictions, your data is transferred to and processed in those locations.
            </p>
            <p>
              We rely on standard contractual clauses and the privacy frameworks of our service providers to ensure adequate data protection during transfers.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 8 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            8. YOUR RIGHTS
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Depending on your jurisdiction, you have some or all of the following rights:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Access:</strong> Request a copy of any personal data we hold about you.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Correction:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate data.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Deletion:</strong> Request that we delete your personal data. This applies primarily to contact form submissions and any email correspondence.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Restriction:</strong> Request that we limit how we process your data.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Portability:</strong> Request your data in a structured, machine-readable format.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Objection:</strong> Object to processing of your personal data for analytics or other purposes.</span>
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-[#39FF14] font-bold">-</span>
                <span><strong class="text-white">Cookie opt-out:</strong> Opt out of analytics cookies at any time via your browser settings.</span>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:privacy@cryptobonuslist.com" class="text-[#39FF14] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">privacy@cryptobonuslist.com</a>. We will respond within 30 days.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you believe we have not adequately addressed your concerns, you have the right to lodge a complaint with a data protection supervisory authority in your jurisdiction.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 9 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            9. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              This site is not intended for anyone under 18 years of age. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal data to us through the contact form, email <a href="mailto:privacy@cryptobonuslist.com" class="text-[#39FF14] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">privacy@cryptobonuslist.com</a> and we will delete it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 10 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            10. DO NOT TRACK SIGNALS
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              Some browsers send a "Do Not Track" (DNT) signal with HTTP requests. There is no universal standard for how websites should respond to DNT signals.
            </p>
            <p>
              We respect DNT signals where practical. If your browser sends a DNT signal, our analytics will not track your visit. Essential cookies and server logs still function normally.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 11 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            11. CRYPTOCURRENCY AND BLOCKCHAIN NOTE
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              This site discusses cryptocurrency gambling. We want to be clear about something: we never ask for or handle your wallet addresses, private keys, seed phrases, or any blockchain credentials.
            </p>
            <p>
              If anyone contacts you claiming to be from CryptoBonusList and asks for wallet access, it is a scam. Report it immediately.
            </p>
            <p>
              Blockchain transactions are public by nature. When you deposit crypto at a casino you found through our links, your transaction is recorded on the public blockchain. That is between you and the blockchain. We do not monitor, track, or access any on-chain activity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 12 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            12. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              We update this policy when something changes. The date at the top tells you when it was last modified. We do not send notifications for policy changes since we do not collect email addresses for that purpose.
            </p>
            <p>
              We recommend checking this page periodically if it matters to you. For significant changes, we will post a notice on the homepage for at least 7 days.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 13 -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="font-[Space_Grotesk] text-2xl font-bold mb-4 border-b-[3px] border-[#39FF14] pb-2">
            13. CONTACT
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-[#D4D4D4] font-[Public_Sans] leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              For privacy-related questions, data requests, or concerns: <a href="mailto:privacy@cryptobonuslist.com" class="text-[#39FF14] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">privacy@cryptobonuslist.com</a>
            </p>
            <p>
              For general inquiries, use the <a href="/contact" class="text-[#39FF14] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">contact page</a> or email <a href="mailto:contact@cryptobonuslist.com" class="text-[#39FF14] underline underline-offset-4 decoration-2">contact@cryptobonuslist.com</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
